  "text": "pfeifferi with dual stressors highly down-regulate several CYPs (microsomal CYPs 2J1-like, 2B4-like, 3A29-like, 26A1-like, and mitochondrial CYP12A2-like). Mitochondrial CYP12A2-like is known to metabolize a variety of insecticides and xenobiotics [CITATION_1] . We cannot discount that contribution to the down-regulation of this particular CYP is a result of mitochondrial degradation caused, in part, by niclosamide as noted previously as well as the additional stress of a patent S. mansoni infection.",
